{"article_id":"tpIdW687naQerP4Y","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Former President Bill Clinton said Tuesday","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"President Obama should find a way","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"to keep his oft-repeated promise to the American public","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"that","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"if those","depth":10},{"id":5,"text":"who liked their present health insurance plan","depth":10},{"id":6,"text":"could keep it under Mr. Obama ' s new health care law .","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"\" I personally believe ,","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"even if it takes a change in the law ,","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"the president should honor the commitment","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"that the federal government made to those people","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"and let them keep what they got , \"","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"Mr. Clinton said in an interview with Ozy Media founder Carlos Watson .","depth":5},{"id":13,"text":"Mr. Obama is under fire","depth":5},{"id":14,"text":"for repeatedly saying","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"people would not lose their existing plans under his signature law ,","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"only to walk back the pledge","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"when millions of Americans received cancellation notices","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"saying","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"their coverage will not meet the Affordable Care Act ' s minimum-coverage standards next year .","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"In the interview","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"published Tuesday ,","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"Mr. Clinton said","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"the country is \" better off with this law than without it , \"","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"but there are three problems with its rollout .","depth":7},{"id":25,"text":"First , online glitches suppressed the first several weeks of enrollment , an incident","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"he compared it to the messy debut of the Medicare prescription benefit program under President George W. Bush .","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"Second , he noted","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"that many governors have not opted to expand Medicaid to those","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"making up to 138 percent of the federal poverty level .","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"The federal government will fully pay for the newly eligible population through 2016 ,","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"so Mr. Clinton thinks","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"more GOP governors will \" flip","depth":11},{"id":33,"text":"and start taking \" the money .","depth":11},{"id":34,"text":"The former president said","depth":7},{"id":35,"text":"the cancellation notices round out the series of problems ,","depth":7},{"id":36,"text":"and it may have an outsized effect on younger people , but \" not all young , \"","depth":7},{"id":37,"text":"who make above 400 percent of the federal poverty level","depth":8},{"id":38,"text":"and are not eligible for subsidies","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"to offset their premiums","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"if they buy new coverage on the Obamacare health exchanges .","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"White House press secretary Jay Carney said","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"President Obama agrees with Mr. Clinton ' s advice ,","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"although he stopped short of saying what specific steps the administration might take .","depth":7},{"id":44,"text":"\" The answer is yes ,","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"the president ' s tasked his team with looking at a range of options , \"","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"Mr. Carney said .","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"He said","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"Mr. Obama has ordered his aides \" to look at ways","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"to address that problem \" of people","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"whose policies have been canceled .","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"Mr. Carney was careful to note","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"that in a TV interview last week , Mr. Clinton said","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"that \" we are better off with this law","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"than without it. \"","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"Mr. Obama apologized last week","depth":6},{"id":56,"text":"for people losing their insurance","depth":7},{"id":57,"text":"based on assurances","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"he made .","depth":8},{"id":59,"text":"Political groups with an eye toward the 2014 elections seized on Mr. Clinton ' s remarks .","depth":6},{"id":60,"text":"The conservative Club for Growth put out a statement","depth":8},{"id":61,"text":"asking","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"if Sen. Mark Pryor , an Arkansas Democrat","depth":12},{"id":63,"text":"who faces a tough reelection battle next year ,","depth":12},{"id":64,"text":"will support the Mr. Clinton ' s call","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"for Mr. Obama to consider potential changes to the law","depth":12},{"id":66,"text":"to help people keep their plans","depth":12},{"id":67,"text":"if they want .","depth":11},{"id":68,"text":"\" Because of Obamacare ,","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"thousands of Arkansans have lost their health insurance ,","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"and premiums are doubling , \"","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"club President Chris Chocula said .","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"\" Mark Pryor needs to decide what he thinks","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"is more important : the people of Arkansas or President Obama and his disastrous health care law . \"","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"\" I applaud President Clinton","depth":8},{"id":75,"text":"for joining the bipartisan call","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"for President Obama to keep his promise to the American people , \"","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"House Speaker John A. Bohner , Ohio Republican , said .","depth":7},{"id":78,"text":"\" These comments signify a growing recognition","depth":7},{"id":79,"text":"that Americans were misled","depth":8},{"id":80,"text":"when they were promised that they could keep their coverage under President Obama ' s health care law . \"","depth":8},{"id":81,"text":"Mr. Boehner restated his commitment","depth":5},{"id":82,"text":"to scrapping the law ,","depth":5},{"id":83,"text":"but said","depth":5},{"id":84,"text":"the parties ' difference \" on that point \" should not stop \" reasonable Democrats from working with us","depth":6},{"id":85,"text":"to shield Americans from its most egregious consequences","depth":7},{"id":86,"text":"- like the millions of current health plans","depth":8},{"id":87,"text":"being canceled . \"","depth":8},{"id":88,"text":"The Republican-led House is scheduled to vote Friday on the Keep Your Health Plan Act , a bill","depth":2},{"id":89,"text":"that would let Americans retain their existing health plans","depth":3},{"id":90,"text":"despite Obamacare ' s new standards .","depth":3}],"relations":[{"parent":181,"left":178,"right":180,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":178,"left":131,"right":177,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":131,"left":103,"right":130,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":103,"left":97,"right":102,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":97,"left":0,"right":96,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":96,"left":1,"right":95,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":95,"left":2,"right":94,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":94,"left":3,"right":93,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":93,"left":92,"right":6,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":92,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":102,"left":101,"right":12,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":101,"left":7,"right":100,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":100,"left":8,"right":99,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":99,"left":98,"right":11,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":98,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":130,"left":109,"right":129,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"}